Datset Name - Soccernet Datset
https://www.soccer-net.org/data
The SoccerNet dataset is a large-scale football video understanding dataset designed to support research in automated sports analysis, particularly in event detection, tracking, and player recognition tasks. It is hosted on the official SoccerNet website (https://www.soccer-net.org/). The dataset contains professional broadcast football match data from top-level competitions, along with structured annotations that make it suitable for training deep learning models. These annotations include precise timestamps for key match events such as goals, yellow cards, red cards, substitutions, and penalties, which are primarily used for the event spotting task. In addition to event labels, SoccerNet also provides tracking information that captures player movement across frames using bounding boxes, enabling spatial and tactical analysis of gameplay. Another important component of the dataset is the Re-Identification (ReID) data, which allows models to consistently identify and track the same player across different camera frames during a match. To make computation efficient, SoccerNet also offers precomputed visual embeddings extracted from deep neural networks, which are commonly used instead of raw video inputs for training models. Overall, the dataset is widely used in computer vision research and forms a strong foundation for building AI systems like MatchMind AI, which aim to perform event detection, player tracking, and full match understanding using machine learning techniques.
